This paper is about energy-efficient training of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the training process of CNNs. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as CNNs are widely used in computer vision tasks. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as CNNs are a popular tool in AI research. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes a novel approach to back-propagation that reduces energy consumption. The fifth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses strategies for reducing computation at different levels of the training process, which could be relevant to distributed or parallel computing.
